// Port decisions for the logs+quantities vertical slice (MetaCoding-0p7).
// subsystem ss:761b... = farmOS "Log Type Plugin Registry". The port is a
// local-first event-sourced store (target profile farmos-local-first): log kinds
// are string-tagged EVENTS, not a PHP plugin class hierarchy. Every structural
// punch-list failure below is that one architectural divergence, made auditable.
{"id":"PD-002","date":"2026-07-18","subsystem":"ss:761b7d53e7a231e2cf7a7782","targetElement":"roles[role_id=role:3b5724c1a2a7c9d03ad96e38]","decision":"supersede","supersededSourceIntention":"FarmLogType base-class role: farmOS models each log kind as a plugin CLASS extending a shared FarmLogType base, discovered via the #[LogType] attribute.","rationale":"The port models a log's kind as a string field on an immutable event, not a subclass. There is no base class to extend and no plugin registry to register into — kinds are open data, added without code. This is the core idiom divergence of an event-sourced store vs a Drupal plugin system; value-equivalence (record a harvest → yield total) is preserved, the class taxonomy is not.","author":"deep-executor (MetaCoding-0p7)"}
{"id":"PD-003","date":"2026-07-18","subsystem":"ss:761b7d53e7a231e2cf7a7782","targetElement":"roles[role_id=role:81d68dbc024e348fdf3c8e1a]","decision":"supersede","supersededSourceIntention":"Birth concrete log-type plugin class (and the family Input/Seeding/Medical/Harvest).","rationale":"Concrete per-kind plugin classes collapse to a single generic recordLog(kind,...) path over the event log; 'harvest'/'birth'/etc. are values, not types. The harvest behavior the fixtures assert is preserved; the per-kind class is idiom that does not cross the value line.","author":"deep-executor (MetaCoding-0p7)"}
{"id":"PD-004","date":"2026-07-18","subsystem":"ss:761b7d53e7a231e2cf7a7782","targetElement":"roles[role_id=role:7ae99936dac636c3e6b8ce94]","decision":"supersede","supersededSourceIntention":"Maintenance concrete log-type plugin class (ambiguous role — brief flagged for human review).","rationale":"Same generic-kind collapse as PD-003. The brief flagged this role ambiguous ('Maintenance' domain unclear); as a string kind it needs no disambiguation to port — it is simply another value the store accepts. Confirms the ambiguity was source-idiom, not value-bearing.","author":"deep-executor (MetaCoding-0p7)"}
{"id":"PD-005","date":"2026-07-18","subsystem":"ss:761b7d53e7a231e2cf7a7782","targetElement":"roles[role_id=role:4bd886ce5c852772efea8cb6]","decision":"supersede","supersededSourceIntention":"FarmLabTestTypeInterface config-entity contract for lab-test types.","rationale":"Lab-test-type configuration is out of scope for the logs+quantities value slice (no lab_test fixtures). A config entity classifying test kinds is Drupal configuration idiom; the port carries no configuration-entity layer. Deferred, not dropped in error.","author":"deep-executor (MetaCoding-0p7)"}
{"id":"PD-006","date":"2026-07-18","subsystem":"ss:761b7d53e7a231e2cf7a7782","targetElement":"interface.provides[symbol=modules/core/entity/src/Plugin/Log/LogType/FarmLogType.php::FarmLogType]","decision":"supersede","supersededSourceIntention":"FarmLogType exported as an EXTENDS point (10 external callers extend it).","rationale":"The provided export IS the base class of PD-002. An event-sourced store exposes recordLog/materialized-view reads as its boundary, not an inheritance anchor. The export is consciously not preserved; the value boundary (the oracle adapter contract) is.","author":"deep-executor (MetaCoding-0p7)"}
{"id":"PD-007","date":"2026-07-18","subsystem":"ss:761b7d53e7a231e2cf7a7782","targetElement":"composition_rules[operation_id=op:0914acefcad7515ea04e4435]","decision":"supersede","supersededSourceIntention":"Protocol op 'Maintenance ∘ FarmLogType' (EXTENDS): a concrete log type must extend the base to be discoverable.","rationale":"'Extend the base class to register a log type' is a plugin-discovery order-of-operations contract that does not exist in the port — kinds are registered by appearing in an event, no inheritance step. Superseded together with PD-002/PD-004.","author":"deep-executor (MetaCoding-0p7)"}
{"id":"PD-008","date":"2026-07-18","subsystem":"ss:761b7d53e7a231e2cf7a7782","targetElement":"composition_rules[operation_id=op:81b161e8c80510f9c97c8441]","decision":"supersede","supersededSourceIntention":"Protocol op 'Birth ∘ FarmLogType' (EXTENDS): concrete Birth/Input plugins extend the base.","rationale":"Same plugin-inheritance protocol as PD-007, for the Birth/Input family. No inheritance protocol exists in the event-sourced port; superseded with PD-003.","author":"deep-executor (MetaCoding-0p7)"}
{"id":"PD-009","date":"2026-07-18","subsystem":"ss:761b7d53e7a231e2cf7a7782","targetElement":"functor.cycle_consistency","decision":"preserve-with-note","supersededSourceIntention":"Cycle consistency G(F(s))=s over the member-set-restricted functor between farmOS-PHP and the TS port.","rationale":"Low cycle consistency (0.4–0.5) is a downstream consequence of the paradigm divergence in PD-002..PD-008: with the plugin class hierarchy superseded, the forward/reverse structural maps have little shared shape to agree on. Not an independent defect — an artifact of a deliberate cross-paradigm port. Recorded so the score is read as expected, not as a displaced-match bug.","author":"deep-executor (MetaCoding-0p7)"}
